      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "CELLPHONE (2) set to peak after his two sound runs on the provincial tracks. Stalked the speed when up in trip for a close-up third over 1500m at Kembla Grange. Blinkers go on and ticks plenty of boxes. MADE IN ITALY (6) handy filly yet to finish out of the money in four starts. Sat on the speed with a game first-up third over 1500m at Newcastle. Key jockey change and doesn't have to improve much to win this. LOVE 'N' GLORY (4) total forgive from the wide gate when snagged back and offered little with a poor eighth over 1600m at Warwick Farm. Finally drawn a decent barrier and no shock to see him go close at the good odds. BELLA WAHINE (8) fourth-up for this and expect to see the blinkers do the trick from the inside gate. Slow into stride and never stretched out in the straight with a battling ninth over 1600m at Warwick Farm. Gets another chance at the each way quote.",
